  "prompt": "Which is the best application for editing photos for tablets?",
  "response": "For tablets, some of the best photo editing applications include:\n\n1. Adobe Lightroom\n- Professional-level editing\n- Cloud syncing\n- Available on iOS and Android\n- Powerful and feature-rich\n\n2. Snapseed (by Google)\n- Free\n- Powerful tools\n- User-friendly interface\n- Available on iOS and Android\n\n3. Pixlr\n- Free\n- Multiple editing features\n- Good for quick edits\n- Available on iOS and Android\n\n4. VSCO\n- Popular among photographers\n- Advanced filters\n- Clean interface\n- Available on iOS and Android\n\n5. Canva\n- More than just photo editing\n- Design and layout tools\n- Easy to use\n- Free version available\n- Good for social media graphics\n\n6. Affinity Photo\n- Professional-level editing\n- Desktop-like experience\n- One-time purchase\n- Available on iPad\n\nThe \"best\" app depends on your specific needs, skill level, and whether you prefer free or paid options. For most users, Adobe Lightroom or Snapseed offer an excellent balance of features and usability.",
